<P>It was a <HI>Pede&s;tal</HI> al&s;o, erected to the Honour of <HI>Marcus Aurelius Dia|dochus,</HI> a <HI>Roman</HI> Knight, Chief-Prie&s;t of <HI>A&s;ia,</HI> and of the Temples at <HI>Pergamus;</HI> and during his own time, High-Prie&s;t of his Country; and for his life, Ruler of the Senate, under the mo&s;t God-like Emperour, <HI>Alexander Severus,</HI> &amp;c.</P>
