<P>We were likewi&s;e conducted to the Hou&s;e of <HI>Mu&s;tapha Haga,</HI> one of the Principal Inhabitants; who&s;e Po&s;ts of his Gate are &s;upported by two Marbles: the one whereof maketh <HI>Antoninus Caracalla</HI> the Re|&s;torer of this City. Perhaps, after its Inva&s;ion by <HI>Ari&s;tonicus;</HI> who pretending to be of the Royal Blood, after the Death of <HI>Attalus,</HI> Son of <HI>Philometer,</HI> invaded it, and &s;everal more of the circumjacent Cities. The next is no le&s;s con&s;iderable, for the unu&s;ual Title given to this am|bitious Prince:
&Tgr;&Ogr;&Ngr; &Ggr;&EEgr;&Sgr; &Kgr;&Agr;&Igr; &THgr;&Agr;&Lgr;&Agr;&Sgr;&Sgr;&EEgr;&Sgr; &Dgr;&Egr;&Sgr;&Pgr;&Ogr;&Tgr;&EEgr;&Ngr;,
<HI>Lord of the Earth and Sea.</HI></P>
<PB N="232" REF="83">
<P><FIGURE>
