<P>But that which is mo&s;t curious among the In&s;criptions, is the Name of the God, Protectour of this Place, mentioned no where in Hi&s;tory, but in two Marbles; one in a Burying-place out of the Town, as we came in, turned up&s;ide down; which my Comerade with great pains copied; and therefore de&s;erveth a chief place among his <HI>&V;nknown Gods.</HI> This was the God <HI>Tyrimnus;</HI> who had his Temple and Prie&s;t here, then <HI>Antoninus Claudius Alphinus,</HI> as it is among&s;t his other great Offices expre&s;&s;ed.</P>
