<P>Here we found other In&s;criptions al&s;o; &s;ome upon Stones above Ground, and in the Walls of old Churches; others we found almo&s;t bu|ried in the Ground, and digg'd them out: For we carried a Mattock, and a Spade, u&s;ually from <HI>Athens</HI> with us. Some are Dedications to the Godde&s;&s;es, <HI>Ceres</HI> and <HI>Pro&s;erpina;</HI> &s;ome to the Emperours, as <HI>Marcus Aurelius;</HI> which, for Brevities &s;ake, I &s;hall omit; only I &s;hall add this belonging to the Deities of this, as pertinent to the Illu&s;tration of it.</P>
